.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/31151129/Hope-XCR-lightweight-mountain-bike-brakes_superlight-powerful-CNC-XC-Trail-MTB-brakeset_made-in-UK_details-on-bike-735x420.jpg 735w\"></a></p><p>Hope hasn’t yet mentioned any other (<em>more affordable, for example</em>) version of the new XCR brakes, but the XCR setup manual includes an exploded diagram that shows both carbon &amp; aluminium compatible lever blades. And of course you can still set up the XCRs as 4-piston brakes together with an E4 brake caliper.</p><p>We’ve started riding the new Hope XCR brakes on our local singletrack and tossing them through some urban enduro trails to push them to the limit. With the light X2 calipers &amp; 180mm rotors we have no need to ask for more braking power.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/31151057/Hope-XCR-lightweight-mountain-bike-brakes_superlight-powerful-CNC-XC-Trail-MTB-brakeset_made-in-UK_riding-downhill.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/31151057/Hope-XCR-lightweight-mountain-bike-brakes_superlight-powerful-CNC-XC-Trail-MTB-brakeset_made-in-UK_riding-downhill.jpg\" alt=\"Hope XCR lightweight MTB brakes, superlight &amp; powerful UK-made CNC-machined XC Trail mountain bike brakeset,&nbsp;trail riding\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/31151057/Hope-XCR-lightweight-mountain-bike-brakes_superlight-powerful-CNC-XC-Trail-MTB-brakeset_made-in-UK_riding-downhill.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/31151057/Hope-XCR-lightweight-mountain-bike-brakes_superlight-powerful-CNC-XC-Trail-MTB-brakeset_made-in-UK_riding-downhill-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/upload